President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring January 22, 2018, as National Sanctity of Human Life Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of recognizing the inherent dignity and worth of every person, born and unborn, regardless of disability, gender, appearance, or ethnicity. It highlights the historical suffering caused by attempts to dehumanize certain groups of people and calls for vigilance in protecting the most vulnerable lives. The proclamation also acknowledges the role of science in supporting the case for life and the advancements in medical technologies that allow us to see the humanity of unborn children. It recognizes the efforts of individuals and organizations who work to support pregnant mothers, facilitate adoptions, and offer hope to those considering or recovering from abortions. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to reflect on the value of life, treat others with dignity and compassion, and embrace our common humanity.